	INSERT INTO [dbo].[SkillsModuleVideos](SMVideoId,[Title],[Text],[F4V],[MP4],[OGV],[Type],[TextPosition])VALUES(@SMVideoID,'Venipuncture - Introduction','<p><b>Skill: Venipuncture</b></p><p>This lesson will demonstrate a key nursing procedure through instructional video and text. After viewing it, you will follow up with an assessment tool to ensure that you have learned the technique.</p><p>This skills lesson is a study guide for nursing students. It is not intended and may not be used to provide medical advice, diagnosis, or treatment.</p>','','','',1,0)
	SET IDENTITY_INSERT SkillsModuleVideos OFF
	INSERT INTO [dbo].[SMVideoMapping]([TestId],[SMVideoId],[OrderNumber]) VALUES (@TestId,@SMVideoID,1)

    Set @SMVideoID = @SMVideoID + 1 --42
	SET IDENTITY_INSERT SkillsModuleVideos ON
	INSERT INTO [dbo].[SkillsModuleVideos](SMVideoId,[Title],[Text],[F4V],[MP4],[OGV],[Type],[TextPosition])VALUES(@SMVideoID,'Venipuncture - Introduction','<p>A venipuncture is the insertion of a needle into a vein to collect a blood specimen into a laboratory tube. In this lesson, two nurse experts will guide you through the procedure of obtaining a blood specimen from a client.</p><p>To make it easy for you, we will present this lesson in four parts: </p><p><ul><li>Gathering the equipment you will need</li><li>Locating the site for the blood draw</li><li>Conducting the entire procedure, step-by-step</li><li>Reviewing the key elements</li></ul></p>','Venipuncture_Intro.f4v','Venipuncture_Intro.mp4','Venipuncture_Intro.ogv',2,1)
	SET IDENTITY_INSERT SkillsModuleVideos OFF
	INSERT INTO [dbo].[SMVideoMapping]([TestId],[SMVideoId],[OrderNumber]) VALUES (@TestId,@SMVideoID,2)

    Set @SMVideoID = @SMVideoID + 1 --43
	SET IDENTITY_INSERT SkillsModuleVideos ON
	INSERT INTO [dbo].[SkillsModuleVideos](SMVideoId,[Title],[Text],[F4V],[MP4],[OGV],[Type],[TextPosition])VALUES(@SMVideoID,'Venipuncture - Equipment','<p><b>Equipment</b></p><p>The most complex part of the process is selecting the right laboratory tubes. To make the appropriate choice, ask yourself: Do I want to ensure clotting to produce serum? Or do I want to stop clotting to get the original plasma? </p>Here''s the difference: Plasma is the fluid in which red and white blood cells are suspended; serum is plasma with fibrinogen and other blood clotting factors removed. The different laboratory tubes are color-coded to guide your choice.<p></p>','Venipuncture_Equipment.f4v','Venipuncture_Equipment.mp4','Venipuncture_Equipment.ogv',2,0)
	SET IDENTITY_INSERT SkillsModuleVideos OFF
	INSERT INTO [dbo].[SMVideoMapping]([TestId],[SMVideoId],[OrderNumber]) VALUES (@TestId,@SMVideoID,3)
	
	Set @SMVideoID = @SMVideoID + 1 --44
	SET IDENTITY_INSERT SkillsModuleVideos ON
	INSERT INTO [dbo].[SkillsModuleVideos](SMVideoId,[Title],[Text],[F4V],[MP4],[OGV],[Type],[TextPosition])VALUES(@SMVideoID,'Venipuncture - Equipment','<p>The equipment checklist included eight necessary items:<ul><li>tubes</li><li>gauze pads</li><li>alcohol swabs</li><li>bandage</li><li>needle</li><li>adapter</li><li>tourniquet (Check for latex allergies.)</li><li>gloves (Again, check for latex allergies.)</li></ul></p><p>Here''s one more to remember: sharps container. Before you start the procedure, set up with your sharps container in a handy position. You want to AVOID reaching across your body or your client''s body with used needles.</P>','','','',1,0)
	SET IDENTITY_INSERT SkillsModuleVideos OFF
	INSERT INTO [dbo].[SMVideoMapping]([TestId],[SMVideoId],[OrderNumber]) VALUES (@TestId,@SMVideoID,4)

	Set @SMVideoID = @SMVideoID + 1 --45
	SET IDENTITY_INSERT SkillsModuleVideos ON
	INSERT INTO [dbo].[SkillsModuleVideos](SMVideoId,[Title],[Text],[F4V],[MP4],[OGV],[Type],[TextPosition])VALUES(@SMVideoID,'Venipuncture - Locating the Site','<p><b>Locating the Site</b></p><p>Now you are ready to interact with the client. You work with the client''s non-dominant arm whenever possible. When you watch the video, notice that we have a mixture of right-handed and left-handed clients, just as you will have in your clinical setting.</p>','Venipuncture_LocatingtheSite.f4v','Venipuncture_LocatingtheSite.mp4','Venipuncture_LocatingtheSite.ogv',2,0)
	SET IDENTITY_INSERT SkillsModuleVideos OFF
	INSERT INTO [dbo].[SMVideoMapping]([TestId],[SMVideoId],[OrderNumber]) VALUES (@TestId,@SMVideoID,5)

	Set @SMVideoID = @SMVideoID + 1 --46
	SET IDENTITY_INSERT SkillsModuleVideos ON
	INSERT INTO [dbo].[SkillsModuleVideos](SMVideoId,[Title],[Text],[F4V],[MP4],[OGV],[Type],[TextPosition])VALUES(@SMVideoID,'Venipuncture - Locating the Site','<p>In using the tourniquet, focus on three words: UP, OVER, and UNDER. To tie the tourniquet, you will:</p><p><ul><li>Stretch the band UP.</li><li>Cross the band OVER.</li><li>Loop the band UNDER.</li></ul></p><p>We identified two ways to avoid mistakes that could alter the client''s lab findings. First, ask client to make a steady fist; they should NOT pump the fist, because that would release enzymes. Second, always remove the tourniquet within a minute, since leaving it on more than a minute would destroy blood cells.</p>','','','',1,0)
	SET IDENTITY_INSERT SkillsModuleVideos OFF
	INSERT INTO [dbo].[SMVideoMapping]([TestId],[SMVideoId],[OrderNumber]) VALUES (@TestId,@SMVideoID,6)

	Set @SMVideoID = @SMVideoID + 1 --47
	SET IDENTITY_INSERT SkillsModuleVideos ON
	INSERT INTO [dbo].[SkillsModuleVideos](SMVideoId,[Title],[Text],[F4V],[MP4],[OGV],[Type],[TextPosition])VALUES(@SMVideoID,'Venipuncture - Procedure','<p><b>Procedure</b></p><p>We have assembled the right equipment and located the best site to collect the blood specimen. Now it''s time to put it all together. We start with our always-required infection prevention measures of hand washing and gloving.</p>','Venipuncture_Procedure.f4v','Venipuncture_Procedure.mp4','Venipuncture_Procedure.ogv',2,0)
	SET IDENTITY_INSERT SkillsModuleVideos OFF
	INSERT INTO [dbo].[SMVideoMapping]([TestId],[SMVideoId],[OrderNumber]) VALUES (@TestId,@SMVideoID,7)

	Set @SMVideoID = @SMVideoID + 1 --48
	SET IDENTITY_INSERT SkillsModuleVideos ON
	INSERT INTO [dbo].[SkillsModuleVideos](SMVideoId,[Title],[Text],[F4V],[MP4],[OGV],[Type],[TextPosition])VALUES(@SMVideoID,'Venipuncture - Procedure','<p>Along with demonstrating the procedure, the nursing instructors shared several secrets of success:</p><p><ul><li>Check the tips of your gloves to remove trapped air.</li><li>Place a fresh alcohol swab on the client''s forearm, in case you want to re-palpate the vein.</li><li>Anchor the client''s vein by pulling it down toward you so that the vein does not roll away from you.</li><li>Have the bandage already opened.</li></p>','','','',1,0)
	SET IDENTITY_INSERT SkillsModuleVideos OFF
	INSERT INTO [dbo].[SMVideoMapping]([TestId],[SMVideoId],[OrderNumber]) VALUES (@TestId,@SMVideoID,8)

