	INSERT INTO [dbo].[SkillsModuleVideos](SMVideoId,[Title],[Text],[F4V],[MP4],[OGV],[Type],[TextPosition])VALUES(@SMVideoID,'Blood Pressure - Introduction','<p>In this lesson, we show you how to:</p><p><ul><li>Gather the equipment you will need.</li><li>Identify the names of the parts of the equipment.</li><li>Proceed through the whole process, step-by-step.</li></ul></p>','','','',1,0)
	SET IDENTITY_INSERT SkillsModuleVideos OFF
	INSERT INTO [dbo].[SMVideoMapping]([TestId],[SMVideoId],[OrderNumber]) VALUES (@TestId,@SMVideoID,3)

	Set @SMVideoID = @SMVideoID + 1 --112
	SET IDENTITY_INSERT SkillsModuleVideos ON
	INSERT INTO [dbo].[SkillsModuleVideos](SMVideoId,[Title],[Text],[F4V],[MP4],[OGV],[Type],[TextPosition])VALUES(@SMVideoID,'Blood Pressure - Equipment','<p><b>Equipment</b></p><p>With a blood pressure cuff in one hand, and a stethoscope around your neck, you are all set to take your first blood pressure reading. Listen closely to the nursing instructor’s use of terminology for these parts of the equipment:</p><p><ul><li>Cuff</li><li>Gauge</li><li>Valve</li><li>Ball (bulb)</li></ul></p>','BloodPressure_Equipment.f4v','BloodPressure_Equipment.mp4','BloodPressure_Equipment.ogv',2,0)
	SET IDENTITY_INSERT SkillsModuleVideos OFF
	INSERT INTO [dbo].[SMVideoMapping]([TestId],[SMVideoId],[OrderNumber]) VALUES (@TestId,@SMVideoID,4)

	Set @SMVideoID = @SMVideoID + 1 --113
	SET IDENTITY_INSERT SkillsModuleVideos ON
	INSERT INTO [dbo].[SkillsModuleVideos](SMVideoId,[Title],[Text],[F4V],[MP4],[OGV],[Type],[TextPosition])VALUES(@SMVideoID,'Blood Pressure - Equipment','<p>Most stethoscopes can be used by any nurse. However, you choose the size of the cuff based on the client’s arm circumference:</p><p><ul><li>Small or pediatric for an infant, child, or frail adult</li><li>Medium for a normal size adult</li><li>Large for an obese adult</li></ul></p><p>Remember, size matters!</p>','','','',1,0)
	SET IDENTITY_INSERT SkillsModuleVideos OFF
	INSERT INTO [dbo].[SMVideoMapping]([TestId],[SMVideoId],[OrderNumber]) VALUES (@TestId,@SMVideoID,5)

	Set @SMVideoID = @SMVideoID + 1 --114
	SET IDENTITY_INSERT SkillsModuleVideos ON
	INSERT INTO [dbo].[SkillsModuleVideos](SMVideoId,[Title],[Text],[F4V],[MP4],[OGV],[Type],[TextPosition])VALUES(@SMVideoID,'Blood Pressure - Systolic/Diastolic','<p><b>Systolic Number/Diastolic Number</b></p><p>Now we will show you the two most important concepts in discussing a client’s blood pressure: systole and diastole. The top number is the systolic pressure, which is the MAXIMUM pressure during contraction of the heart. The bottom number is the diastolic pressure, which is the MINIMUM pressure during the heart’s relaxed phase. Think . . . maximum on top, minimum below.</p>','BloodPressure_SystolicDiastolic.f4v','BloodPressure_SystolicDiastolic.mp4','BloodPressure_SystolicDiastolic',2,0)
	SET IDENTITY_INSERT SkillsModuleVideos OFF
	INSERT INTO [dbo].[SMVideoMapping]([TestId],[SMVideoId],[OrderNumber]) VALUES (@TestId,@SMVideoID,6)

	Set @SMVideoID = @SMVideoID + 1 --115
	SET IDENTITY_INSERT SkillsModuleVideos ON
	INSERT INTO [dbo].[SkillsModuleVideos](SMVideoId,[Title],[Text],[F4V],[MP4],[OGV],[Type],[TextPosition])VALUES(@SMVideoID,'Blood Pressure - Systolic/Diastolic','<p>The nursing instructor summed up in two sentences the key to taking an accurate blood pressure:</p><p><ul><li>Note the first tapping sound, to get the systolic pressure.</li><li>Note when the tapping sound disappears, to get the diastolic pressure.</li></ul></p>','','','',1,0)
	SET IDENTITY_INSERT SkillsModuleVideos OFF
	INSERT INTO [dbo].[SMVideoMapping]([TestId],[SMVideoId],[OrderNumber]) VALUES (@TestId,@SMVideoID,7)

	Set @SMVideoID = @SMVideoID + 1 --116
	SET IDENTITY_INSERT SkillsModuleVideos ON
	INSERT INTO [dbo].[SkillsModuleVideos](SMVideoId,[Title],[Text],[F4V],[MP4],[OGV],[Type],[TextPosition])VALUES(@SMVideoID,'Blood Pressure - Procedure','<p><b>Procedure</b></p><p>Now that we know which two numbers we want, let’s watch the instructor go slowly through the whole procedure. Be sure to note the tips for inflating the cuff just enough to occlude the brachial artery. They’ll help you take an accurate reading AND assure your client’s comfort!</p><p>After this part of the video, we will highlight the most critical steps in the sequence. Then we’ll share some useful tips for running your blood pressure procedure smoothly.</p>','BloodPressure_Procedure.f4v','BloodPressure_Procedure.mp4','BloodPressure_Procedure.ogv',2,0)
	SET IDENTITY_INSERT SkillsModuleVideos OFF
	INSERT INTO [dbo].[SMVideoMapping]([TestId],[SMVideoId],[OrderNumber]) VALUES (@TestId,@SMVideoID,8)

	Set @SMVideoID = @SMVideoID + 1 --117
	SET IDENTITY_INSERT SkillsModuleVideos ON
	INSERT INTO [dbo].[SkillsModuleVideos](SMVideoId,[Title],[Text],[F4V],[MP4],[OGV],[Type],[TextPosition])VALUES(@SMVideoID,'Blood Pressure - Procedure','<p>That procedure list identified these critical steps to remember:</p><p><ul><li>Bell over brachial.</li><li>Tapping begins = systolic pressure.</li><li>Tapping stops = diastolic pressure.</li><li>Systolic over diastolic.</li></ul></p>','','','',1,0)
	SET IDENTITY_INSERT SkillsModuleVideos OFF
	INSERT INTO [dbo].[SMVideoMapping]([TestId],[SMVideoId],[OrderNumber]) VALUES (@TestId,@SMVideoID,9)

		Set @SMVideoID = @SMVideoID + 1 --118
	SET IDENTITY_INSERT SkillsModuleVideos ON
	INSERT INTO [dbo].[SkillsModuleVideos](SMVideoId,[Title],[Text],[F4V],[MP4],[OGV],[Type],[TextPosition])VALUES(@SMVideoID,'Blood Pressure - Procedure','<p>Together we have identified the essential steps to taking an accurate blood pressure reading. Now here are some tips to help you glide through the procedure:</p><p><ul><li>Get a snug fit of the cuff around the upper arm.</li><li>Position the gauge where you can read it.</li><li>Inflate the cuff to 30 mm Hg above EITHER the client’s usual systolic number OR the point when the brachial pulse is no longer palpable.</li><li>Hold the bell of the stethoscope against the client’s arm with your index finger and middle finger.</li><li>Take your time. . . . Go as slowly as you need to go.</li><li>Practice! Practice! Practice!</li></ul></p><p>Rehearsing the procedure until you’ve got it will take the pressure off of you!</p>','','','',1,0)
