    SET @TestId=1403 -- Dressing Changes and Sterile Technique
	Set @SMVideoID = @SMVideoID + 1 --119
	SET IDENTITY_INSERT SkillsModuleVideos ON
	INSERT INTO [dbo].[SkillsModuleVideos](SMVideoId,[Title],[Text],[F4V],[MP4],[OGV],[Type],[TextPosition])VALUES(@SMVideoID,'Dressing Changes and Sterile Technique - Introduction','<p><b>Skill: Dressing Changes and Sterile Technique</b></p><p>This lesson will demonstrate a key nursing procedure through instructional video and text. After viewing it, you will follow up with an assessment tool to ensure that you have learned the technique.</p><p>This skills module is a study guide for nursing students. It is not intended and may not be used to provide medical advice, diagnosis, or treatment.</p>','','','',1,0)
	SET IDENTITY_INSERT SkillsModuleVideos OFF
	INSERT INTO [dbo].[SMVideoMapping]([TestId],[SMVideoId],[OrderNumber]) VALUES (@TestId,@SMVideoID,1)
	
	Set @SMVideoID = @SMVideoID + 1 --120
	SET IDENTITY_INSERT SkillsModuleVideos ON
	INSERT INTO [dbo].[SkillsModuleVideos](SMVideoId,[Title],[Text],[F4V],[MP4],[OGV],[Type],[TextPosition])VALUES(@SMVideoID,'Dressing Changes and Sterile Technique - Introduction','<p>In a dressing change, the nurse cleanses, protects, and monitors a client’s wound. The dressing change begins in a non-sterile environment to remove the previous dressing, then progresses to a sterile environment to place and adhere a new dressing over the wound. In this lesson, our experienced nurse instructor Lela Cunningham will guide you through three dressing change procedures: wet-to-dry dressings, hydrocolloid dressings, and transparent dressings.</p>','','','',1,0)
	SET IDENTITY_INSERT SkillsModuleVideos OFF
	INSERT INTO [dbo].[SMVideoMapping]([TestId],[SMVideoId],[OrderNumber]) VALUES (@TestId,@SMVideoID,2)
	
	Set @SMVideoID = @SMVideoID + 1 --121
	SET IDENTITY_INSERT SkillsModuleVideos ON
	INSERT INTO [dbo].[SkillsModuleVideos](SMVideoId,[Title],[Text],[F4V],[MP4],[OGV],[Type],[TextPosition])VALUES(@SMVideoID,'Dressing Changes and Sterile Technique - Wet-to-Dry Dressings','<p>We start with Lela applying a wet-to-dry dressing composed of gauze and tape, with the possible addition of packing tape for a deeper wound. Lela has already performed the required infection prevention measures of hand washing and gloving with disposable exam gloves. She has also placed an absorbent pad with a waterproof backing under the client’s wound site, to protect the bed linens. As she performs a wet-to-dry dressing change, notice that she has gathered all her supplies on a tray and has a biohazardous disposal container handy.</p>','Wet_to_Dry_Dressing.f4v','Wet_to_Dry_Dressing.mp4','Wet_to_Dry_Dressing.ogv',2,0)
	SET IDENTITY_INSERT SkillsModuleVideos OFF
	INSERT INTO [dbo].[SMVideoMapping]([TestId],[SMVideoId],[OrderNumber]) VALUES (@TestId,@SMVideoID,3)

	Set @SMVideoID = @SMVideoID + 1 --122
	SET IDENTITY_INSERT SkillsModuleVideos ON
	INSERT INTO [dbo].[SkillsModuleVideos](SMVideoId,[Title],[Text],[F4V],[MP4],[OGV],[Type],[TextPosition])VALUES(@SMVideoID,'Dressing Changes and Sterile Technique - Wet-to-Dry Dressings','<p>Once again, here are the supplies you need for any wet-to-dry dressing change:</p><p><ul><li>exam gloves</li><li>sterile gloves</li><li>sterile saline and syringe</li><li>sterile gauze dressings</li><li>tape (precut to the desired length)</li><li>biohazard waste container</li></ul></p><p>For a deeper wound, your  wet-to-dry supplies would also include packing strips, along with sterile scissors and sterile hemostat to handle the packing strips without contamination.</p>','','','',1,0)
	SET IDENTITY_INSERT SkillsModuleVideos OFF
	INSERT INTO [dbo].[SMVideoMapping]([TestId],[SMVideoId],[OrderNumber]) VALUES (@TestId,@SMVideoID,4)

	Set @SMVideoID = @SMVideoID + 1 --123
	SET IDENTITY_INSERT SkillsModuleVideos ON
	INSERT INTO [dbo].[SkillsModuleVideos](SMVideoId,[Title],[Text],[F4V],[MP4],[OGV],[Type],[TextPosition])VALUES(@SMVideoID,'Dressing Changes and Sterile Technique - Wet-to-Dry Dressings','<p>Lela proceeds smoothly in removing and reapplying the dressing, since she has done this procedure many times before. Since she will be showing you two more types of dressing applications, you will be able to see her repeat the entire process for each type.</p>','','','',1,0)
	SET IDENTITY_INSERT SkillsModuleVideos OFF
	INSERT INTO [dbo].[SMVideoMapping]([TestId],[SMVideoId],[OrderNumber]) VALUES (@TestId,@SMVideoID,5)

	Set @SMVideoID = @SMVideoID + 1 --124
	SET IDENTITY_INSERT SkillsModuleVideos ON
	INSERT INTO [dbo].[SkillsModuleVideos](SMVideoId,[Title],[Text],[F4V],[MP4],[OGV],[Type],[TextPosition])VALUES(@SMVideoID,'Dressing Changes and Sterile Technique - Hydrocolloid Dressings','<p><b>Hydrocolloid Dressings</b></p><p>The dressing itself is the main difference between a hydrocolloid and wet-to-dry dressing changes. Hydrocolloid dressings are opaque, so you cannot see the wound. They have a gel on the underside of the dressing that absorbs drainage. This improves both healing activity and wearing time of the dressing. Let’s watch Lela apply a hydrocolloid dressing to a client’s leg wound.</p>','Hydrocolloid_Dressing.f4v','Hydrocolloid_Dressing.mp4','Hydrocolloid_Dressing.ogv',2,0)
	SET IDENTITY_INSERT SkillsModuleVideos OFF
	INSERT INTO [dbo].[SMVideoMapping]([TestId],[SMVideoId],[OrderNumber]) VALUES (@TestId,@SMVideoID,6)

	Set @SMVideoID = @SMVideoID + 1 --125
	SET IDENTITY_INSERT SkillsModuleVideos ON
	INSERT INTO [dbo].[SkillsModuleVideos](SMVideoId,[Title],[Text],[F4V],[MP4],[OGV],[Type],[TextPosition])VALUES(@SMVideoID,'Dressing Changes and Sterile Technique - Hydrocolloid Dressings','<p>Once you place the nontransparent hydrocolloid dressings on the wound, you cannot observe the condition of the wound. So, after any kind of wound dressings are removed, inspect the client’s wound for:</p><p><ul><li>Size and depth.</li><li>Tissue appearance (tissue type, color, odor, drainage).</li><li>Condition of the surrounding skin.</li></ul></p><p>Avoid making wrinkles as you smooth the dressing around the wound. They could provide tunnels for leakage of wound drainage. The next dressing type also needs wrinkle-proofing. However, it has the added benefit of allowing continuous monitoring of the stages of wound healing.</p>','','','',1,0)
	SET IDENTITY_INSERT SkillsModuleVideos OFF
