	 VALUES(@QID,'','','N009302','02','2','4','4','4','2','3','7','0','3','','<p>The nurse provides care for a newly delivered infant with a temperature of 97.2 <sup>o</sup>F 
	(36.2<sup>o</sup>C).   Which actions will the nurse take when caring for this newborn?</p><p><b>Select all that 
	apply.</b></p>','<P>1) <B>CORRECT</B> -  Infant needs to be warmed.  Skin-to-skin maternal-infant contact can help raise the 
	infant’s temperature.</P> <P>2)  Cover the couplet with a warmed blanket.  Blankets for newborns with a low temperature need to be pre-warmed; blankets from the linen cart are not pre-warmed. </P>
