	 VALUES(@QID,'','','N009317','02','4','9','4','4','3','3','3','0','3','','<p>The emergency department nurse admits the client reporting a severe headache.  The nurse notes right-sided weakness and the client is hypertensive.  Which nursing actions must the nurse implement in the first hour of care?</p><p><b>Select all that apply.</b></p>','<P>1) Client admitted with indicates of a stroke.  The patient will remain NPO until the diagnostic studies are complete.  </P><P>2) Physical therapy may be involved because the patient has right-sided weakness. However, the consultation will not occur within the first hour because the patient is not yet stable.</P>
	<P>3)  <B>CORRECT</B> - A complete blood count will be ordered to evaluate for any internal hemorrhaging and use of clotting factors during the initial phase of a stroke.  </P> <P>4)  <B>CORRECT</B> - A CT scan can detect for differences between and ischemic and hemorrhagic stroke, as well as the size and location of the stroke.  </P> 
	<P>5)  <B>CORRECT</B> - A lumbar puncture may be ordered for detection of blood in the cerebral spinal fluid.</P> 
	<P>6)  <B>CORRECT</B> - An IV is necessary at a slow rate so medications can be delivered intravenously if needed.  Fluid 

