	<p>2) <b>CORRECT</b>— Osmotic diuresis can occur with hyperglycemia, so urine output must be monitored closely.   </p>
	<p>3) Weight gain may be related to the diabetes, but would not occur because of administering D<sub>50</sub>.  </p>
	<p>4) If osmotic diuresis occurs, the patient may become hypotensive.  </p>
	<p>5) Heart palpitations and tachycardia are often symptoms seen with hypoglycemia. </p>
	<p>6) <b>CORRECT</b>— D<sub>50</sub> should be administered through a large bore needle, as extravasation of the solution can cause tissue sloughing and necrosis. </p>

