	 VALUES(@QID,'','','n009332','02','4','7','0','4','3','3','7','0','2','',' <p>The nurse provides care to the client with receiving total parenteral nutrition (TPN) with insulin through a central venous catheter.  The nurse should include which actions in the client’s plan of care?  </p>
	<p><b>Select all that apply.</b></p>
	',' <p>1) <b>CORRECT</b>— A client receiving TPN with insulin may develop osmotic diuresis if the blood glucose gets too high.  Monitoring intake and output (I & O) helps the nurse to determine fluid volume balance in the patient receiving TPN.  </p>
	<p>2) <b>CORRECT</b>— A client receiving TPN with insulin may develop osmotic diuresis if the blood glucose gets too high.  Monitoring daily weights helps the nurse to determine fluid volume balance in the patient receiving TPN.  </p>
	<p>3) In the event a bag of TPN is not readily available, the substitute solutions are D<sub>10</sub>W or D<sub>20</sub>W.  </p>
	<p>4) TPN tubing must be changed every 24 hours to decrease the risk of infection.  </p>
	<p>5) <b> CORRECT</b>— Because the client is receiving TPN with insulin, FSBG supplies are necessary in the event of hyper/hypoglycemia.  </p>
	<p>6) If the infusion of TPN is behind prescribed rate, the infusion should never be infused faster. This action could result in shifts in fluid and electrolytes.  </p>


	','','1396','total parenteral nutrition (TPN)','2','2',0,0,0,0,0,0,'','03','','','','','','','','','','','','','',1,-1,'E','','','','','','','','',0,0)

